rules.natural: If the customer invests in stocks, then they receive dividends from stocks.
Under the condition that the customer pays low fees, they get portfolio rebalancing.

If the customer uses a mobile app, then either they achieve financial goals or if the absence of the implication that using a robo-advisor leads to paying low fees holds, the customer experiences technical issues.
Either the customer uses a mobile app, or they visit a branch.

Whenever the customer visits a branch, then either they achieve financial goals, or if it is not the case that using a robo-advisor results in paying low fees, then technical issues are experienced by the customer.
Provided that the customer owns high-risk assets in stocks, they do not receive dividends from stocks.
If the customer has a financial advisor, then whenever they invest in stocks, they own high-risk assets in stocks.
Either the customer qualifies for premium service, or they have a financial advisor.
Under the condition that the customer has credit issues, it is not the case that they qualify for premium service.
Under the condition that the customer receives automated advice, they have a financial advisor.
Provided that the customer gets portfolio rebalancing, they receive automated advice.
Whenever it is not the case that using a robo-advisor leads to paying low fees, it is not the case that the customer experiences technical issues.
Provided that the customer does not have initial capital, they invest in stocks.
